description: Compare Low German nubben (“to knock, cuff”).

examples: Harvey saw with disgust that there were no sheets on his bed-place. He was lying on a piece of dingy ticking full of lumps and nubbles.

verbs.description: nubble (third-person singular simple present nubbles, present participle nubbling, simple past and past participle nubbled)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To beat or bruise with the fist.
